data.content:
noun
plural ~ -cies
the average number of years that a person or animal can expect to live [noncount]
improvements in diet that have resulted in greater life expectancy for many people [count]
calculating the life expectancies of different social groups - often used figuratively
What is the life expectancy of a new computer? [=how long can a new computer be expected to last or be useful?]
tuổi thọ trung bình (của một hạng người, theo thống kê)
